properties.headline: Winter Storm Watch issued February 7 at 2:37AM CST until February 9 at 6:00PM CST by NWS La Crosse WI
properties.description:
...Snow Likely Sunday...Travel Impacts Expected...

.A winter storm will bring snow to the area from late Saturday
night through Sunday. Accumulations of 6 or more inches are
possible. Currently, the higher amounts look more likely in the
Interstate 90 corridor with much of that falling in the morning.

Those will travel plans this weekend should play close attention
to the latest forecasts. Be prepared to alter or delay travel if
conditions warrant. Those with flexible plans may want to consider
consolidating them on Saturday to avoid likely travel impacts
Sunday.

* WHAT...Heavy snow possible with accumulations of 5 to 7 inches
possible.

* WHERE...Portions of central, southwest and west central
Wisconsin.

* WHEN...From Sunday morning through Sunday afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult.
properties.instruction: Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WATCH IN EFFECT FROM SUNDAY MORNING THROUGH SUNDAY AFTERNOON
